description:
Juju hats are a beautiful home decor trend, also know as the Bamiléké feather headdress or Tyn Hat.

The texture and colour's make any wall look amazing.

These hats originate from Cameroon, Africa and have been reserved for royalty and prominate leaders among tribes. They symbolise prosperity & are believed to possess the positive qualities of birds and the beauty as well as fragility of life.  

The headdress are made of natural or dyed chicken feathers or of wild bird (such as guinea fowl) feathers stitched onto a woven raffia support. They are easy to store when not in use as they fold up.
